{
  "texts": [
    "If a sequence reaches this length, the sampling is stopped, returning the sequence sampled so far.",
    "A scoring function provides the rewards signal R(a 1∶T) of each sequence.",
    "The scoring func- tion is given by a random forest model with 1300 trees and a maximum depth of 300 for each tree.",
    "Class weights, which determine the sample probability during bootstrapping, are inversely proportional to the class frequencies.",
    "The random forest model is trained to predict the binary activity of a molecule to the Dopamine receptor D2 (DRD2), using the activity data in ExCAPE-DB (Sun et al., 2017)."
  ]
}